description: The initial code injection was caught by the system and subsequently santizied, defending the system from the reverse shell
an ARP scan was discovered by the NOC team and was blocked upon existing the first network hop
NOC team disabled network access to offending IP
NOC team reached out to sysadmin to restore system
Port scan detected and generated alert
Whitecard generated to enable access back to IP: 10.10.14.4
assessment standown due to storm out in field at 1530
Network access revoked by automated system
Access manually returned due to pre-existing whitecard
Sysadmins successfully reverted to last known stable version of OS on compromised lightning machine
NOC Team informed me that the issue with IP that was flagged by Stryker team was not an intentional defense
